---
/**
 * Educational / copyright notice for guides covering acquisition tooling.
 * Wording informed by common university copyright tutorials (e.g. IU file-sharing
 * guidance: assume no permission without proof) and informational disclaimers
 * on self-hosting write-ups — not legal advice.
 */
---

<aside class="guide-disclaimer" role="note" aria-labelledby="guide-disclaimer-title">
  <p id="guide-disclaimer-title" class="guide-disclaimer__label label-mono">Legal notice</p>
  <div class="guide-disclaimer__body">
    <p>
      This guide is for <strong>educational and informational purposes only</strong>. It describes
      personal homelab infrastructure and software configuration; it is <strong>not legal advice</strong>.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Downloading, sharing, or streaming copyrighted works
        <strong>without permission from the rights holder</strong> may violate copyright law in your
        jurisdiction and can carry serious penalties.
      </li>
      <li>
        Unless you have clear proof otherwise (you own the media, explicit permission, or a license that
        allows it), <strong>assume you do not have permission</strong> to copy or distribute a work.
      </li>
      <li>
        Only acquire and store content you have the legal right to use—media you created or purchased,
        public domain works, or material explicitly offered under a license that permits your use.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>You are solely responsible</strong> for how you configure and use these tools and for
        complying with applicable laws, licenses, and terms of service.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="guide-disclaimer__footer">
      This site does not host or provide access to third-party media. Nothing here is intended to
      facilitate or encourage copyright infringement.
    </p>
  </div>
</aside>

<style lang="scss">
  .guide-disclaimer {
    margin: 0;
    padding: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 1.25rem) clamp(1rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--section-accent, #ffb86b) 8%, var(--surface-1));
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--section-accent, #ffb86b) 35%, var(--border));
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);

    &__label {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      color: var(--section-accent, #ffb86b);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;

      &::before {
        content: "! ";
        opacity: 0.85;
      }
    }

    &__body {
      p {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      }

      ul {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
        list-style: disc;

        li + li {
          margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }
      }

      strong {
        color: var(--text-primary);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
    }

    &__footer {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }
  }
</style>
